The paper discusses the implementation of the Apriori algorithm on the MapReduce framework, which is commonly used for large-scale distributed data processing. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC), Database (cs.DB), and Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper discusses the performance and optimization of the algorithm, which could also place it in the Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Cryptography and Security (cs.CR) sub-categories.
